cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.LG 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it deals with the security of user-chosen PINs. It could also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as it studies the effects of blacklists on user behavior and frustration. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with the security of personal devices and information. The paper also touches upon the topic of balancing usability and security, which could place it under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
